Leaders from the United States, the European Union, and several European countries have reaffirmed their commitment to negotiating a Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership agreement. They aim to build upon their existing economic partnership to promote sustainable growth, job creation, and increased international competitiveness. The leaders emphasize the strategic importance of the agreement and see it as an opportunity to promote shared principles and values, such as transparency and joint approaches to global trade challenges. They commend the progress made by negotiators thus far and urge them to continue making strides in the coming year.